          "type": "reasoning",
          "text": "I can see the alerts.mdx file content. It documents alerts with:\n\n1. **Examples**: 8 contextual types (primary, secondary, success, danger, warning, info, light, dark)\n2. **Live example**: With dismiss button\n3. **Link color**: Using `.alert-link` class\n4. **Additional content**: With headings, paragraphs, dividers\n5. **Icons**: With Bootstrap Icons\n6. **Dismissing**: Using `.alert-dismissible`, `.fade`, `.show` classes and `data-bs-dismiss=\"alert\"`\n\nLooking at the example code in the docs:\n```html\n<div class=\"alert alert-primary\" role=\"alert\">\n  A simple primary alert—check it out!\n</div>\n```\n\nAnd for dismissible:\n```html\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning alert-dismissible fade show\" role=\"alert\">\n  <strong>Holy guacamole!</strong> You should check in on some of those fields below.\n  <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"alert\" aria-label=\"Close\"></button>\n</div>\n```\n\nNote that the close button in Bootstrap 5 is NOT a `<button>` element with class `btn-close` - it IS a button with `btn-close` class. The `data-bs-dismiss=\"alert\"` triggers the dismiss behavior.\n\nLooking at our current alert.php - we have:\n- `alert alert-{type}` - correct\n- `alert-dismissible fade show position-relative` - added when dismissible\n- `role=\"alert\"` - correct\n- Close button uses `btn-close position-absolute top-0 end-0` - should work\n\nBut looking at our implementation again - when we set `dismissible=true` and add a close button with `append_child_tail`, the close button goes to the end of child elements. But the message text is set via `set_value()` which sets the content of the div itself.\n\n\nFor dismissible alerts, the Bootstrap structure places the close button after the alert content as a sibling, not nested within it. The `btn-close` class positions it absolutely at the top-right corner. When the alert is dismissible, I need to append the close button as a child element so it renders after the message text. For dismissible alerts, the `set_value()` call happens before adding the heading and close button, so they get appended after the text content. However, since the close button has absolute positioning with `top-0 end-0`, it renders in the top-right regardless of DOM order.\n\nThe user specifically requested help implementing PHP objects that comply with official Bootstrap documentation, so I should prioritize following the Bootstrap implementation rather than other approaches.\n",
