          "text": "Looking at the Bootstrap docs, the card structure in the docs has:\n- header is inside a `card-header` div but NOT always present as the first child\n- body is the main content area\n- footer is optional\n\nLooking at the Bootstrap example:\n```html\n<div class=\"card\">\n    <div class=\"card-header\">\n      Featured\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card-body\">\n      <h5 class=\"card-title\">Special title treatment</h5>\n      <p class=\"card-text\">With supporting text below as a natural lead-in to additional content.</p>\n      <a href=\"#\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Go somewhere</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n```\n\nThe header should be the first child, but only if explicitly set. The current card implementation has header always created but empty.\n\nAlso, looking at the card-text class on p elements, I see that `card-text` is used but in Bootstrap 5 the correct class is `card-text` on a `<p>` element. The current code uses `$this->body->append_p($text, 'card-text');` which should be correct.\n\nHowever, the card has header, body, footer all always appended even if empty. This could cause issues.\n\nLet me also check the footer - in Bootstrap docs, the footer is a `card-footer` div which is placed after body.\n\nThe current implementation:\n1. Always creates header, body, footer\n2. Always appends all three in that order\n\nBut in Bootstrap docs, some cards don't have header or footer. The card body is the essential part.\n\nLet me fix the card to only append header and footer if they have content, or provide methods to set them.\n\nAlso I notice card-subtitle should have `mb-2` class for spacing between title and subtitle.\n\nLet me update the card.php file:\n",
