          "text": "Looking at the buttons.mdx spec, I see several key things about button groups with checkboxes and radios:\n\n1. Checkbox toggle buttons - using `.btn-check`\n2. Radio toggle buttons - using `.btn-check`\n\nThe button_group currently just accepts any button objects and adds them. According to the spec, when creating checkbox or radio button groups, the structure is:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"btn-group\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"Basic checkbox toggle button group\">\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"btn-check\" id=\"btncheck1\" autocomplete=\"off\">\n    <label class=\"btn btn-outline-primary\" for=\"btncheck1\">Checkbox 1</label>\n    ...\n</div>\n```\n\nSo the button_group should also be able to handle checkbox/radio input+label pairs. But looking at the current implementation, it just appends buttons.\n\nActually, looking more closely at button-group.mdx (which I fetched earlier), it shows that for checkbox/radio button groups, the structure uses inputs with `.btn-check` class paired with labels. \n\nThe button_group class currently accepts array of button objects and appends them. The Bootstrap spec for checkbox/radio groups uses a different pattern - the buttons in the group are not traditional `.btn` buttons but `<input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"btn-check\">` paired with `<label class=\"btn\">`.\n\nSo the button_group should support:\n1. Regular button objects (current behavior)\n2. Checkbox/radio inputs with `.btn-check` class and corresponding labels\n\nLet me update the button_group to support checkbox and radio button groups as per the spec. Looking at the buttons.mdx spec, for checkbox toggle buttons:\n\n```html\n<input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"btn-check\" id=\"btncheck1\" autocomplete=\"off\">\n<label class=\"btn btn-outline-primary\" for=\"btncheck1\">Checkbox 1</label>\n```\n\nAnd radio buttons:\n\n\n```html\n<input type=\"radio\" class=\"btn-check\" name=\"btnradio\" id=\"btnradio1\" autocomplete=\"off\" checked>\n<label class=\"btn btn-outline-primary\" for=\"btnradio1\">Radio 1</label>\n```\n\nThe current implementation only handles button objects, but I need to support the checkbox/radio pattern as well. I should add methods for checkbox and radio groups that handle the input+label pairs properly, allowing for checked/disabled states and proper association via for/id attributes.\n",
