on children rather than the nested ul/li structure we currently have. This means I should reconsider how the nav element is structured when appended as a child of the wrapper div. The issue is that the UL element is being appended as a child of the wrapper div, but Bootstrap expects the wrapper div to have the `nav` class and contain the buttons directly, not wrapped in a UL. Since our nav class extends ul, we need to restructure this so the wrapper div contains the buttons rather than the UL itself. The UL structure works for basic nav, but breaks when we try to use it inside a flex container for vertical layouts - we need the wrapper to be the nav element and append buttons directly to it instead. Bootstrap expects the buttons to be direct children of the nav element, not wrapped in li tags. The current implementation outputs buttons inside li elements, which doesn't match the expected structure. I need to modify create_vertical_pills to append buttons directly without the li wrapper to align with Bootstrap's documentation.",
